content.problem:
A clock has a minute hand 10 inches long. How far does the tip of 
the minute hand travel in 20 minutes?

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.8]
 (0,0) circle (2);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (2pt);

 % Clock face marks
 in {0,30,...,330} {
 (:1.8) – (:2);
 }

 % Minute hand at 12
 (0,0) – (90:2);
 % Minute hand at 20 min position (120° from 12)
 (0,0) – (-30:2);

 % Arc traveled
 (90:2) arc (90:-30:2);

 at (90:2.2) {12};
 at (-30:2.2) {4};
tikzpicture
center

A chord is 6 cm from the center of a circle with radius 10 cm. 
Find the length of the chord.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.8]
 (0,0) circle (2.5);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (2pt) node[below left] {$O$};

 % Chord
 (-2,1.5) – (2,1.5);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (-2,1.5) circle (2pt) node[left] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (2,1.5) circle (2pt) node[right] {$B$};

 % Perpendicular from center
 (0,0) – (0,1.5);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,1.5) circle (2pt) node[above right] {$M$};

 % Radius to A
 (0,0) – (-2,1.5);

 % Labels
 at (-0.2,0.75) {$6$};
 at (-1,0.75) {$10$};

 % Right angle
 (-0.15,1.5) – (-0.15,1.35) – (0,1.35);
tikzpicture
center
